Question: Stage of microbial growth wherein there is an equilibrium between dividing cells and dying cells
CorrectExplanation:
Microbial Growth Phases

  • Lag Phase: Organisms are adjusting to the environment.

  • Log Phase/Logarithmic Phase/Exponential Phase: Division is at a constant rate.

  • Stationary Phase: Dying and dividing organisms are at an equilibrium

  • Death/Decline Phase: More deaths than New cells
IncorrectExplanation:
Microbial Growth Phases

  • Lag Phase: Organisms are adjusting to the environment.

  • Log Phase/Logarithmic Phase/Exponential Phase: Division is at a constant rate.

  • Stationary Phase: Dying and dividing organisms are at an equilibrium

  • Death/Decline Phase: More deaths than New cells

Question: Primary health care pertains to?
CorrectExplanation:
• Primary Healthcare: involves EVERYDAY HEALTHCARE given by general medical doctors and nurses who act as the FIRST CONTACT with a patient for non-emergency situations

  • Secondary Healthcare: pertains to health services by specialized medical professionals who are typically the SECOND CONTACT with a patient, often referred from the primary healthcare provider

• Primary Healthcare: involves EVERYDAY HEALTHCARE given by general medical doctors and nurses who act as the FIRST CONTACT with a patient for non-emergency situations

Question: Measures degree of unsaturation
CorrectExplanation:
Assay of Fatty Acids

  • Acid value - mg of KOH needed to NEUTRALIZE free acids

  • Ester Value - mg of KOH needed to SAPONIFY ESTERS in 1 gram of sample

  • Saponification value/Koettsdorfer number - mg of KOH needed to NEUTRALIZE AND SAPONIFY the esters in 1 gram of sample

  • Iodine value - measures UNSATURATED FATTY ACIDS
IncorrectExplanation:
Assay of Fatty Acids

  • Acid value - mg of KOH needed to NEUTRALIZE free acids

  • Ester Value - mg of KOH needed to SAPONIFY ESTERS in 1 gram of sample

  • Saponification value/Koettsdorfer number - mg of KOH needed to NEUTRALIZE AND SAPONIFY the esters in 1 gram of sample

  • Iodine value - measures UNSATURATED FATTY ACIDS

Which of the following indices represents the index that measures the number of individuals who have died within a susceptible population during a specific period because of a particular disease?
CorrectExplanation:
• Prevalence rate: the total number of cases of a disease existing in a population 

  • Virulence: the quantitative ability of an agent to cause disease

  • Mortality rate: the number of deaths due to a disease divided by the total population

  • Morbidity rate: the number of individual who have become ill because of a specific disease within a susceptible population during a specific period
IncorrectExplanation:
• Prevalence rate: the total number of cases of a disease existing in a population 

  • Virulence: the quantitative ability of an agent to cause disease

  • Mortality rate: the number of deaths due to a disease divided by the total population

  • Morbidity rate: the number of individual who have become ill because of a specific disease within a susceptible population during a specific period
